<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="110" type="note">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
The only species known from the Guianas that would agree with 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Meyer’s">Meyer's</normalizedToken>
description is 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Feuillet" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Feuillet" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Euploca" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Euploca humilis" order="Boraginales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Euploca humilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Foerther, H" journalOrPublisher="Sendtnera" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" pagination="35 - 241" publicationUrl="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/52056page/1/mode/2up" refId="B15" refString="Foerther, H, 1998. Die infragenerische Gliederung der Gattung Heliotropium L. und ihre Stellung innerhalb der subfam. Heliotropioidea (Schrad.) Arn. (Boraginaceae). Sendtnera 5: 35 - 241, http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/52056page/1/mode/2up" title="Die infragenerische Gliederung der Gattung Heliotropium L. und ihre Stellung innerhalb der subfam. Heliotropioidea (Schrad.) Arn. (Boraginaceae)." url="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/52056page/1/mode/2up" volume="5" year="1998">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Förther">Foerther</normalizedToken>
(1998
</bibRefCitation>
: 238) lists 
<taxonomicName authority="L., 1774" authorityName="Feuillet" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Feuillet" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Messerschmidia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Messerschmidia incana" order="Boraginales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="incana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Messerschmidia incana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Feuillet" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Feuillet" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Heliotropium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Heliotropium ternatum" order="Boraginales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ternatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Heliotropium ternatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[= 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Feuillet" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Feuillet" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Euploca" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Euploca humilis" order="Boraginales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Euploca humilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
] with a question mark, but Meyer placed a synonym in the protolog of his new species, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Tournefortia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Tournefortia sessilifolia" order="Boraginales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sessilifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Tournefortia sessilifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Poir. (1804: 360), a species described from Argentina. Because 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Tournefortia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="sessilifolia" order="Boraginales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sessilifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">sessilifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was available in 
<taxonomicName authority="L., 1774" authorityName="L." authorityYear="1774" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Messerschmidia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Messerschmidia" order="Boraginales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Messerschmidia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it should have been used as the epithet. Therefore the name by Meyer is not validly published.
</paragraph>
